question: How has Nvidia's data center revenue changed over the past year?
ground_truth: Nvidia's data center revenue has grown significantly, driven by AI GPU demand. The segment has shown consistent triple-digit growth rates throughout FY2024-2025.

NVIDIA Data Center Revenue Analysis - Past Year
 Revenue Performance by Quarter
| Quarter | Data Center Revenue | YoY Growth | QoQ Growth |
|---------|---------------------|------------|------------|
| Q4 FY25 | $35.6B | 78% | 16% |
| Q3 FY25 | $30.8B | 94% | 17% |
| Q2 FY25 | $26.3B | 122% | - |
 Key Highlights
Exceptional Growth Trajectory:
- Data Center revenue grew from $26.3B in Q2 FY25 to $35.6B in Q4 FY25, representing a 35% increase over three quarters
- YoY growth remained extremely strong, ranging from 78% to 122% across the reported periods
- Data Center consistently represents ~90% of total company revenue
Segment Dominance:
- Q4 FY25: Data Center ($35.6B) vs. Gaming ($2.5B) - Data Center is 14x larger
- Q3 FY25: Data Center ($30.8B) vs. Gaming ($3.3B)
- Q2 FY25: Data Center ($26.3B) vs. Gaming ($2.9B)
 Cash Generation Supporting Growth
The strong Data Center performance drove exceptional cash flow:
- Q4 FY25: Free cash flow of $15.5B
- Q2 FY26: Free cash flow of $13.5B  
- Q3 FY26: Free cash flow of $22.1B
